  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with potentially significant legal consequences, which can include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Possible prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Complexity of the scheme\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the case\n\nProsecution is typically handled by federal agencies like the Department of Justice or FBI.\n\nNote: This is general legal information and not specific legal advice. Actual consequences can vary significantly based on individual circumstances.",
